cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with capacity region of a communication channel with delayed channel state information. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses a two-user channel and the capacity-achieving strategies of sub-problems must be interleaved and carried on simultaneously. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possibility as the paper deals with communication between two users. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possibility as the paper mentions the multicast channel as a sub-problem. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possibility as the paper may involve complexity analysis of the capacity-achieving strategies.
